Curried Sweet Potato Soup
  --Cook's Country

1/4 c evov, divided
3 1/2 tsp curry powder, divided
3 garlic cloves, minced, divided
1 tbsp grated fresh ginger, divided
4 1/2 c water
2 lb sweet potatoes, peeled, halved lengthwise, and sliced 1/4" thick
14 oz can coconut milk
1/2 c white miso
1 tsp table salt, divided
1/3 c raw pepitas
1/8 tsp cayenne pepper

Heat 2 tbsp oil in large saucepan over medium heat until shimmering. Add 1 tbsp curry powder, 2 garlic cloves, and 2 tsp ginger and cook until fragrant, ~30 s. Add water, sweet potatoes, coconut milk, miso, and 3/4 tsp salt and bring to simmer over high heat. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer until potatoes are very tender, ~15 min. Meanwhile, cook pepitas, cayenne, and remaining 2 tbsp oil, 1/2 tsp curry powder, and 1/4 tsp salt in 8" skillet over medium heat until pepitas are golden, 3-5 min. Stir in remaining garlic and ginger and cook until fragrant, ~30 s. Set aside. Using immersion blender, blend soup until smooth, about 2 minutes. Serve soup drizzled with spiced oil and pepitas.
